Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 181, 49 Name Klenostratos.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1128)
